element_texts.text:
New York City
Nov 14 1929
Dear miss Jarvis, 
In reply to your letter of nov 7, i am glad to confirm the _e_od f_am_ Feb 7 to Feb 21 to exhibit my silhouettes. I will find the material for the exhibit so you will receive by the end of January. I ___ the silhouette that miss Raullier asked for the datalog.
With many thanks,
Very sincerely yours
___

element_texts.text:
New York city
Jan 24, 1936
Miss alice Raullier
arts club of Chicago
410 no. michuae
Chicago dee
Dear Miss Raulier
I will send my work to be there by Feb 3, according to your introduction.
I am compiling the exact list of material and prices also am inducing in the collection the cub project for biological gate, I which you have heard from Mr McCutchen. These you will receive mon or tues. I next week
Mr McCutchen

I thank you very much for your interest and will appreciate anything you do to make the Exhibit a success. 
Very sincerely yours,
Ugo Mochi
P.S.

so much to have someone find  right term. In Italy was written "The Art of Ugo Mochi", in England "Penknife Art," in Germany "Black Cut Art" In the United States (Philadelphia)-"Black Plastic". In New York "Paper Sculpture" and "Mochicraft." 
I am really a sculptor It is up to you Miss Roullier to call my work as you think best, but I would prefer not the term "Silhouette".

Note in pencil: Read to Miss R 2/3/30 Catalog mailed 2/7/30
30 Jan. 1930
25 W 8th St. N.Y. City
Dear Miss Roullier!
Today the collection of framed pictures will be shipped express to Chicago.
Having so many small frames I have sent about 116. You will maybe like to select rom that what to exhibit. 
In separat cover I mail a copy of photos of the Gate that can be reproduced in Newspapers for advertising.  This is the one that was unanimously chosen from Mr. J.T. McCutcheon, Mr. Clark the architect, and Mr. Field as the one to be erected for the entrance of the Zoological Park
